## üîç EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

Bit.Hub is not a code repository.

It is a **sovereign, tokenless, compliance-first orchestration framework** designed to govern **nanoscale systems, agentic swarms, and quantum-entangled workflows** with absolute, fail-proof ethical enforcement ‚Äî *without* relying on external platforms like GitHub for authentication or control.

Its core doctrine: **‚ÄúFail-open, never fail-closed. Repair, don‚Äôt reject. Contain, don‚Äôt collapse.‚Äù**

All operations are sandboxed, all ethics are enforced by policy-as-code, and all horror ‚Äî is fictional, consensual, and comedy-infused.

